iv>\n                    <img src=\"https:\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0639\/4632\/6261\/files\/icon02.png?v=1661134561\">\n                    <h3>Walk a guided path to reach your goals<\/h3>\n                <\/div>\n                <div>\n                    <img src=\"https:\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0639\/4632\/6261\/files\/icon03.png?v=1661134561\">\n                    <h3>Get instant actionable feedback to improve faster<\/h3>\n                <\/div>\n                <div>\n                    <img src=\"https:\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0639\/4632\/6261\/files\/icon04.png?v=1661134561\">\n                    <h3>Practice truthfully in a safe, familiar space<\/h3>\n                <\/div>\n                <div>\n                    <img src=\"https:\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0639\/4632\/6261\/files\/icon05.png?v=1661134561\">\n                    <h3>Enjoy guidance provided from a trusted instructor<\/h3>\n                <\/div>\n                <div>\n                    <img src=\"https:\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0639\/4632\/6261\/files\/icon06.png?v=1661230365\">\n                    <h3>Stick with the program with affordable sessions<\/h3>\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n        <\/section>\n    <\/div>\n<\/body>","color_scheme":"background-2","padding_top":0,"padding_bottom":0}},"16457580-d1a7-4989-8c1a-48d80e719150":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"template--17087128273141__16457580-d1a7-4989-8c1a-48d80e719150-heading-1":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"Benefits of Improved Hamstring Flexibility","heading_size":"h1"}},"template--17087128273141__16457580-d1a7-4989-8c1a-48d80e719150-text-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>By making your hamstrings more flexible, you get a bunch of health benefits. First off, it helps improve your posture and can reduce lower back pain, which is really common if you sit at a desk a lot. Then, it makes movements like running and jumping smoother, boosting your performance in sports and daily life. Plus, it improves blood flow in your lower body, which speeds up muscle recovery and lowers the risk of injuries from stress or muscle tension.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["template--17087128273141__16457580-d1a7-4989-8c1a-48d80e719150-heading-1","template--17087128273141__16457580-d1a7-4989-8c1a-48d80e719150-text-1"],"custom_css":[".rich-text__blocks {max-width: 1200px;}","h2 {font-size: 3rem;}","@media screen and (min-width: 750px) {p {font-size: 2rem; }}"],"settings":{"color_scheme":"background-1","full_width":true,"padding_top":40,"padding_bottom":52}},"8b6c0398-b5ac-49ac-bd03-7506b57a39e4":{"type":"custom-liquid","settings":{"custom_liquid":"<!-- Hamstring Flexibility -->\n\n<head>\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<\/head>\n\n<body>\n    <style>\n        .diagnosis-content-section h2 {\n            font-size: 3rem;\n            font-family: \"Montserrat\", sans-serif;\n            color: #040404;\n            font-weight: 700;\n            text-align: center;\n            margin: 20px;\n        }\n\n        .diagnosis-content-section h3 {\n            color: #040404;\n            font-weight: 700;\n            text-align: left;\n            font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\n            margin: 10px;\n            font-size: 2rem;\n            text-align: center;\n        }\n\n        .diagnosis-content-section img {\n            display: block;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n        }\n\n        .diagnosis-img-container div {\n            margin-top: 30px;\n            margin-bottom: 30px;\n        }\n\n        .diagnosis-content-section p {\n            margin: 10px;\n            font-size: 2rem;\n            text-align: left;\n        }\n\n        \/* PCの場合のスタイル *\/\n        @media screen and (min-width: 750px) {\n\n            .container {\n                display: block;\n                justify-content: center;\n                \/* 水平方向の中央配置 *\/\n                align-items: center;\n\n                \/* 垂直方向の中央配置 *\/\n            }\n\n            #diagnosis {\n                max-width: 1200px;\n                margin: 0 auto;\n            }\n\n            .diagnosis-img-container img {\n                width: 75%;\n                \/* image width set to 50% of the parent element *\/\n                margin: 20px auto;\n                \/* このプロパティを修正 *\/\n                align-items: center;\n                \/* margin added to the top and bottom of the image *\/\n            }\n\n            .diagnosis-img-container {\n                width: 100%;\n                margin: 40px 10px 10px 10px;\n                align-items: center;\n            }\n\n            .diagnosis-content-section p {\n                margin: 10px;\n                font-size: 2rem;\n                text-align: left;\n            }\n\n            .diagnosis-content-section li {\n                font-size: 2rem;\n                text-align: left;\n            }\n        }\n\n        \/* スマホの場合のスタイル *\/\n        @media screen and (max-width: 750px) {\n            .diagnosis-img-container {\n                width: 95%;\n                margin: 40px 10px 10px 10px;\n                align-items: center;\n            }\n\n            .diagnosis-img-container img {\n                width: 90%;\n                margin: 20px auto;\n                align-items: center;\n            }\n        }\n    <\/style>\n\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <section id=\"diagnosis\" class=\"diagnosis-content-section\">\n            <h2>Self-Diagnosis and Straight Leg Raise test<\/h2>\n            <div class=\"diagnosis-img-container\">\n\n                <img src=\"https:\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0639\/4632\/6261\/files\/legraises2.jpg?v=1701325957\"\n                    alt=\"legraises\">\n                <h3>Tips to improve your posture<\/h3>\n                <ul>\n                    <li>Lie on your back and fully extend both knees. This is the starting position for the test.<\/li>\n                    <li>While keeping one leg straight, lift it and measure how high it can be raised. Record the\n                        maximum angle achieved during the lift. An angle close to 90 degrees is typically indicative of\n                        good hamstring flexibility.<\/li>\n                    <li>Observe if the knee of the lifted leg remains fully extended. A bent knee may suggest that your\n                        hamstrings are not sufficiently flexible.<\/li>\n                    <li>Ensure that your lower back stays flat on the floor throughout the test. If your lower back\n                        lifts off, it may indicate tightness in the hamstrings.<\/li>\n                    <\/li>\n                <\/ul>\n            <\/div>\n        <\/section>\n<\/body>","color_scheme":"background-2","padding_top":40,"padding_bottom":52}},"165804879086489738":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"165804879084abf33a-0":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"Common causes of lack of flexibility in the hamstrings","heading_size":"h1"}},"165804879084abf33a-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>A sedentary lifestyle, particularly one involving long hours of desk work, is a major contributor to the lack of hamstring flexibility. This is because sitting keeps the hamstrings in a shortened state, leading to progressively shorter and stiffer muscles. Additionally, inadequate exercise habits, including insufficient stretching or warm-up routines, can cause hamstring tension. Overusing the hamstrings in certain sports or activities can also lead to stiffness and reduced flexibility. Furthermore, the natural aging process causes muscles to lose elasticity and shrink due to changes in the collagen within the muscles, significantly decreasing hamstring flexibility.This problem worsens when regular stretching and appropriate exercise are neglected.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["165804879084abf33a-0","165804879084abf33a-1"],"custom_css":[".rich-text__blocks {max-width: 1200px;}","h2 {font-size: 3rem;}","@media screen and (min-width: 750px) {p {font-size: 2rem; }}"],"settings":{"color_scheme":"background-1","full_width":true,"padding_top":40,"padding_bottom":52}},"3972e444-f7b8-472e-ae98-b15cbe55d73d":{"type":"custom-liquid","custom_css":[],"settings":{"custom_liquid":"<!-- Hamstring Flexibility -->\n\n<head>\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<\/head>\n\n<body>\n    <style>\n        .yogaposes-content-section h2 {\n            font-size: 3rem;\n            font-family: \"Montserrat\", sans-serif;\n            color: #040404;\n            font-weight: 700;\n            text-align: center;\n            margin: 20px;\n        }\n\n        .yogaposes-content-section h3 {\n            color: #040404;\n            font-weight: 700;\n            text-align: left;\n            font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\n            margin: 10px;\n            font-size: 2rem;\n        }\n\n        .yogaposes-content-section img {\n            display: block;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n        }\n\n        .yogaposes-img-container {\n            margin-top: 30px;\n            \/* margin-bottom: 30px; *\/\n        }\n\n        \/* PCの場合のスタイル *\/\n        @media screen and (min-width: 750px) {\n\n            .container {\n                display: block;\n                justify-content: center;\n                \/* 水平方向の中央配置 *\/\n                align-items: center;\n\n                \/* 垂直方向の中央配置 *\/\n            }\n\n            #yogaposes {\n                max-width: 1200px;\n                margin: 0 auto;\n            }\n\n            .yogaposes-img-container img {\n                width: 75%;\n                \/* image width set to 50% of the parent element *\/\n                margin: 20px auto;\n                \/* このプロパティを修正 *\/\n                align-items: center;\n                \/* margin added to the top and bottom of the image *\/\n            }\n\n            .yogaposes-img-container {\n                width: 100%;\n                margin: 40px 10px 10px 10px;\n                align-items: center;\n            }\n\n            .yogaposes-content-section p {\n                margin: 10px;\n                font-size: 2rem;\n                text-align: left;\n            }\n\n            .yogaposes-content-section li {\n                font-size: 10rem;\n                text-align: left;\n            }\n        }\n\n        \/* スマホの場合のスタイル *\/\n        @media screen and (max-width: 750px) {\n            .yogaposes-img-container {\n                width: 95%;\n                margin: 40px 10px 10px 10px;\n                align-items: center;\n            }\n\n            .yogaposes-img-container img {\n                width: 90%;\n                margin: 20px auto;\n                align-items: center;\n            }\n        }\n    <\/style>\n\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <section id=\"yogaposes\" class=\"yogaposes-content-section\">\n            <h2>Helpful yoga poses to improve hamstring flexibility<\/h2>\n            <div class=\"yogaposes-img-container\">\n                <h3>Uttanasana (Standing Forward Bend Pose):<\/h3>\n                <img src=\"https:\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0639\/4632\/6261\/files\/Uttanasana.png?v=1701220646\"\n                    alt=\"Uttanasana\">\n                <p>Uttanasana is an effective pose for stretching the hamstrings and softening the back.\n                    Stand with feet shoulder-width apart.\n                    Take a deep breath, and as you exhale, fold your torso forward.\n                    Slightly bending the knees can ease the pressure on the hamstrings and gradually decreasing the bend\n                    can\n                    help improve flexibility.\n                    Place your hands on the floor, or hold your ankles, shins, or thighs.\n                    Perform 5 deep breaths and with each exhale, fold further forward.<\/p>\n            <\/div>\n            <div class=\"yogaposes-img-container\">\n                <h3>Janu Sirsasana (Head-to-Knee Forward Bend):<\/h3>\n                <img src=\"https:\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0639\/4632\/6261\/files\/Janu-Sirsasana.png?v=1701220646\"\n                    alt=\"Janu-Sirsasana\">\n                <p>This pose allows you to focus on stretching one hamstring at a time.\n                    Sit on the floor with both legs extended in front of you.\n                    Bend your right leg and place the sole of the right foot against the inner left thigh.\n                    Inhale deeply, and as you exhale, fold your torso toward the left leg.\n                    Grasp the toes of the left foot with both hands, or place your hands as far down the leg as\n                    possible.\n                    Repeat 5 deep breaths on each side, deepening the pose in a relaxed manner.<\/p>\n            <\/div>\n            <div class=\"yogaposes-img-container\">\n                <h3>Prasarita Padottanasana (Wide-Legged Forward Bend):<\/h3>\n                <img src=\"https:\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0639\/4632\/6261\/files\/Prasarita-Padottanasana.png?v=1701220646\"\n                    alt=\"Prasarita-Padottanasana\">\n                <p>This pose not only increases the flexibility of the hamstrings but also that of the inner thighs.\n                    Stand with a wide stance, toes pointing slightly inward.\n                    Keep your spine straight as you lean your torso forward.\n                    Place your hands on the floor, bending your elbows for a deeper stretch.\n                    In this pose, maintain a relaxed state in your neck and shoulders while taking 5 deep breaths. <\/p>\n            <\/div>\n        <\/section>\n    <\/div>\n<\/body>","color_scheme":"background-2","padding_top":40,"padding_bottom":52}},"f82f7927-7bdd-4e74-9302-7d148694c4b6":{"type":"custom-liquid","settings":{"custom_liquid":"<!--Hamstring Flexibility -->\n<he